  <tr>
    <td valign="top" ><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div>
		
			<font face="verdana" size="2">
			
		<font face="verdana" size="2"><b>Weight:</b>&nbsp; </font><font face="verdana" size="2">0.1&nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
	
		
		
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td align="left">  
  	
	<font face="verdana" size="2">Beast:&nbsp; </font><font face="verdana" size="2"><a href="http://www.everlore.com/bestiary/beastdetails.asp?mode=show&amp;BID=2124">Will o' Wisp</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
	
	</td>
  </tr>
  <tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
  <tr>
    <td align="left" valign="top"><font face="Verdana" size="2">
    The EQ team decided that it was far too easy to make money off of the wisps.  So they decreased the number of regular and greater lightstones found on wisps and put a NoSaveLightstone on all the wisps without Lighstones or Greater Lightstones.  Then apparently the NoSaveLightstones were too useful, so they changed it and now most wisps are carrying Burned Out Lightstones. These sell for 1cp! They give no light and they cannot be dropped.
		
		
		</font>
    </td>
  </tr>
  
</table><br>
