			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To answer the real question of what use is the Burned out lightstone. Yes it has a use, Yes it can be valuable to you and No Variant did not screw this up.<BR>
For those of you that arent true casters it is usles for you to loot it unless you want a cheep light.<BR>
However when you take the Greater Lightstone and 2 Lightstones to the Gypsies in South Ro you get the Concordance of Research and 2 Books on Runes and Research. Volume 1 Tells you how to use the Concordance of Research and Vol 2 tells you what Component's you need to combine to for a Practice Rune. you make 2 practice Runes, an Azia and Beza and then combine them to make a completed Practice reun. as you progress in levels you need to go to the next harder practice reune to advance in that skill. the BURNED OUT LIGHTSTONE is one of the cmponents for one of the practice reuns and no the quest isnt broken. it can be valuable to you in this sence. if you combine a practice reune and go up a skill lvl you dont have to spend good plat on a practice point in you're guild. for me it costs now 8 plat to use 1 point in the guild on research, so it saves me money. At the same time I can use my points now everytime I lvl to go into something else becides Researching spells. some of the components can outweigh the cost of the point for me at 8 plat but by useing the Concordance of Research I am able to use the practice points in my guild for other things.<BR>
Playing Everquest is'nt just about how much loot you can get on a kill it's about adventure and discovering things, if you all Quested a bit more you would find out that some of these things you call worthless are infact more valuable then you realy thought. Also a vald reason for the Burned Out Lightstone being NO DROP is that is't for a Quest. how boreing would quests become if we could just go buy all our quest materials. Also every server has an economey according to Variant. if people started selling Quest items that were no drop the prices would go out of control. by doing this No Drop on what you concider worthless items they maintain that people that need these items can get them readly and dont find a group of people farming them for enormouse proffits and thus quest item components remain cheeper then the quest item.
				</font>
			</td>

